# Wiring guide

## Pin assignments

| Component | Arduino pin |
|---|---|
| Green LED (signal) | Pin 8 |
| Red LED (signal) | Pin 4 |
| Buzzer | Pin 9 |
| Green button | Pin 7 |
| Red button | Pin 6 |
| FSR 402 (analog read) | A0 |
| All grounds | GND via breadboard rail |

## Grip strength sensor (FSR 402) — voltage divider

The FSR's resistance drops as pressure increases. To read it as a voltage on an analog pin, build a voltage divider:

1. One FSR leg → Arduino 5V
2. Other FSR leg → same breadboard row as a jumper wire to A0
3. From that same row, one leg of a 10kΩ resistor
4. Other leg of the 10kΩ resistor → GND

Note: FSR 402 legs are flat ribbon-style and can be unreliable in breadboards — ensure firm, direct contact, or use small clip leads if connections are intermittent.

## LED + button wiring (per color)

- Long leg (anode) of LED → signal pin, through a 220Ω resistor
- Short leg (cathode) of LED → GND rail
- One button terminal → digital pin (configured `INPUT_PULLUP`)
- Other button terminal → GND rail
